<subSubSection pageId="89" pageNumber="90" type="types">
<paragraph pageId="89" pageNumber="90">Types.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="89" pageNumber="90">Milan et al. (1974: 89) indicated a holotype, but it is uncertain whether the specimen actually derives from the original type series and whether it was the only specimen Brusina had at hand. The specimen is stored in the Croatian Natural History Museum, Zagreb, coll. no. 2988-634.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="89" pageNumber="90" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="89" pageNumber="90">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="89" pageNumber="90">
Introduced for 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Olivier" authorityYear="1804" class="Gastropoda" family="Melanopsidae" genus="Melania" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Melania costata" order="Pteropoda" pageId="89" pageNumber="90" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="costata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="89" pageNumber="90">Melania costata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sensu Neumayr, 1969, non Olivier, 1804. 
<bibRefCitation author="Wenz, W" journalOrPublisher="Gastropoda extramarina tertiaria" pageId="333" pageNumber="334" pagination="2503 - 2886" refId="B542" refString="Wenz, W, 1929. Fossilium Catalogus I: Animalia. Gastropoda extramarina tertiaria vol. IX: 2503 - 2886" title="Fossilium Catalogus I: Animalia." volume="vol. IX" year="1929">Wenz (1929)</bibRefCitation>
considered all records of &quot; 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Olivier" authorityYear="1804" class="Gastropoda" family="Melanopsidae" genus="Melania" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Melania costata" order="Pteropoda" pageId="89" pageNumber="90" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="costata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="89" pageNumber="90">Melania costata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
&quot; from the Pliocene of Slavonia to represent the same species and synonymized them with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pallary" authorityYear="1916" class="Gastropoda" family="Melanopsidae" genus="Melanopsis" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Melanopsis abbreviata subsp. cosmanni" order="Pteropoda" pageId="89" pageNumber="90" phylum="Mollusca" rank="subSpecies" species="abbreviata" subSpecies="cosmanni">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="89" pageNumber="90">Melanopsis abbreviata cosmanni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Obviously, he was unaware that 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Brusina" authorityYear="1884" class="Gastropoda" family="Melanopsidae" genus="Melanopsis" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Melanopsis croatica" order="Pteropoda" pageId="89" pageNumber="90" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="croatica">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="89" pageNumber="90">Melanopsis croatica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Brusina, 1884 is the first available name for them (see also discussion of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Oppenheim" authorityYear="1890" class="Gastropoda" family="Melanopsidae" genus="Melanopsis" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Melanopsis pseudocostata" order="Pteropoda" pageId="89" pageNumber="90" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="pseudocostata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="89" pageNumber="90">Melanopsis pseudocostata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Oppenheim, 1890).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
